<!-- §8 Why people are buying — problem this solves -->
<h2>Why Do Wine Glasses Keep Breaking — and What's the Fix?</h2>
<p>Standard wine glasses are made to look good on a table, not to survive the real world. A single careless reach, a gust of wind at a picnic, or a toddler nearby — and $20 worth of stemware is in pieces on your patio. For anyone who actually drinks wine outside of a formal dining room, fragile glass creates constant low-level stress.</p>
