<h2>How Do You Use a Stainless Steel Wine Glass?</h2>
<div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.25rem;margin:1.25rem 0;">
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">1</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Choose your finish and set size</strong><p>Select from Golden, Stainless Steel, or Rose Gold finish. Buy a single glass to try it, a 2-pack for couples, or a 6-pack for entertaining. The Golden finish is the most popular for gifting; Stainless Steel is the most versatile day-to-day.</p></div></div>
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">2</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Pre-chill before pouring white wine or rosé</strong><p>Place the empty glass in the freezer for 10 minutes before pouring. The double-wall vacuum insulation will then maintain cold temperature for up to 2 hours outdoors. For red wine, no pre-chilling needed — just pour and enjoy.</p></div></div>
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">3</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Hand wash or top-rack dishwasher only</strong><p>Hand washing is recommended to preserve the finish, especially for Golden and Rose Gold variants. If using a dishwasher, top rack only. Avoid abrasive scrubbers — a soft sponge keeps the finish looking new longer.</p></div></div>
</div>

